HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 552
By Boyd
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Dorothy Steffen on the
celebration of her 100th birthday.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we pay tribute to those citizens who are celebrating special
occasions in their estimable lives; and
WHEREAS, Dorothy Steffen will celebrate her 100th birthday on October 6, 2025, a
milestone that will be commemorated as yet another precious souvenir of life's rich pageant;
and
WHEREAS, Dorothy Steffen was born on October 6, 1925, in Cuba, Missouri; the
youngest of six children, she spent her childhood on a farm and feed mill owned by her father;
and
WHEREAS, she attended school in Cuba before moving to Rolla, Missouri, where she
graduated from high school and took secretarial classes; and
WHEREAS, Dorothy Steffen met her future husband, Lee Steffen, in Rolla, where he
was attending seminary to become a Missouri Synod Lutheran minister; the young couple was
joined in holy matrimony in 1945 after Mr. Steffen finished his vicarage; and
WHEREAS, Reverend Steffen's first church was in Clearwater, Nebraska; moving there
shortly after their marriage, the Steffens lived in Nebraska for six years and welcomed three
sons; and
WHEREAS, Reverend and Mrs. Steffen next moved to Spencer, Iowa, where their fourth
son was born; and
WHEREAS, Dorothy Steffen loved the life of a homemaker and pastor's wife, despite the
frequent relocations; in 1964, the Steffens moved to a new church in Lakeland, Florida, where
they served faithfully until 1988; and
