WHEREAS, after their twenty-four-year tenure in Florida, the Reverend and Mrs. Steffen
moved to Franklin, North Carolina, where they enjoyed their home in the mountains and a semi-
retired life; and
WHEREAS, following her beloved husband's passing in 2008, Dorothy Steffen continued
to live independently for many years; and
WHEREAS, after experiencing a fall in 2023, Mrs. Steffen moved to Tennessee to live
with her third son, Paul, and eventually transitioned to American House in Lebanon; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Steffen has always enjoyed Tennessee, often visiting her son and his
family here over the years, and she is happy to now call the Volunteer State home as she
celebrates a century of life filled with love, faith, and family; and
WHEREAS, this proud matriarch has nine grandchildren and nineteen great-
grandchildren scattered about the United States and Australia; and
WHEREAS, we wish to grasp this golden opportunity to specially recognize one of
Tennessee's most outstanding citizens on this very special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Dorothy Steffen on the celebration of her 100th
birthday and extend to her our best wishes for much continued success and happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
